
● Summary

  I've implemented a complete system for hierarchical MOC → KU generation:

  1. New MOC Parser (core/utils/moc_parser.py)

  - Parses markdown headings (H2-H6) into a tree structure
  - Extracts YAML frontmatter for MOC metadata
  - Provides generate_ku_yaml_from_heading() to create KU files

  2. Updated Docs Components (components/docs_components.py)

  - Added level, children, parent_slug to TopicInfo
  - New render_hierarchical_topics() method for collapsible nested navigation

  3. Updated Docs Routes (adapters/inbound/docs_routes.py)

  - Now dynamically parses the MOC file instead of hardcoded topics
  - Sections and topics come directly from H2/H3/H4/H5/H6 headings
  - Hierarchical navigation shows nested structure

  4. KU Generation Script (scripts/generate_kus_from_moc.py)

  # Dry run to see what would be created
  poetry run python scripts/generate_kus_from_moc.py --dry-run

  # Generate all KUs
  poetry run python scripts/generate_kus_from_moc.py

  # Generate for specific section
  poetry run python scripts/generate_kus_from_moc.py --section stories

  5. KU YAML Schema with MOC Membership

  Each generated KU includes:
  moc:
    uid: moc:worldview
    section: environment-sustainability-weather
    path: environment-sustainability-weather/food-agriculture
    heading_level: 4

  This links the KU back to its position in the MOC taxonomy.

  To view the changes:

  Visit http://localhost:8000/docs - sections now come from the MOC, and clicking a section shows hierarchical collapsible topics instead of flat lists.
